    <string name="help_text_part1"><![CDATA[&#160;&#160;This app <u><b><big>does not</big></b></u> collect any of your information and contains no networking functions. Continuing to use means you agree to the above privacy policy.<br/>&#160;&#160;This app requires Shizuku installed and activated on your device.<br/>&#160;&#160;In later use, you can <u><b><big>long press</big></b></u> the cat icon on the main screen title (as shown below) to open this help screen.]]></string>
    <string name="app_features">App Features</string>
    <string name="help_text_part2"><![CDATA[&#160;&#160;--Tap to edit an entry; long press to copy the saved command.<br/><br/>&#160;&#160;--<u><b><big>Single tap</big></b></u> the cat icon on the title to switch to one‑time command mode.<br/><br/>&#160;&#160;--Tap either of the two Shizuku status buttons on the main screen title to <u><b><big>refresh Shizuku status</big></b></u>. Closing and reopening the app also works.<br/><br/>&#160;&#160;--If Shizuku is started with root, this app will also run commands with root. If you prefer <u><b><big>not to use such high privilege</big></b></u>, you can check “Drop root to shell” in the command edit dialog to run commands with shell privileges only.<br/><br/>&#160;&#160;--Tap the Settings button at the bottom of this screen to explore more features!]]></string>
